During a press briefing, White House Press Secretary Sarah Sanders announced that President Trump has accepted the Speaker's invitation to deliver the State of the Union Address on January 30th. She also discussed the importance of giving back during the holiday season and mentioned the President's donation of his third-quarter salary to the Department of Health and Human Services (HHS). Acting Secretary Hargan from HHS then spoke about the President's donation and how it will be used to combat the opioid crisis. Sanders also addressed questions about the President's relationship with Secretary of State Tillerson, tax reform, North Korea, the President's tweets, and the President's health.